{{Orphan|date=February 2009}} '''Hans Try''' (1934&ndash;1990) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] archivist and historian.
He hailed from [[Søgne]]. He started as an [[ethnologist]], but later took the [[cand.philol.]] degree in history. He worked in the [[National Archival Services of Norway|National Archival Services]] branch in Kristiansand from 1975. His main work was ''To kulturer - en stat. 1851-1884'', volume eleven of the overview of Norwegian history, ''Norges historie'', published by [[J.W. Cappelens Forlag|Cappelen]]<ref name=aft>{{cite news|title=Hans Try|last=Repstad|first=Laurits|date=16 March 1990|work=[[Aftenposten]]}}</ref> and edited by [[Knut Mykland]].
He was a deputy board member of the [[Norwegian Institute of Local History]] from 1986 to 1989 and of the [[Norwegian Archive, Library and Museum Authority|Staet Museum Council]] from 1987 to 1990.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nsd.uib.no/polsys/data/forvaltning/utvalg/person/16327|title=Hans Try|publisher=Norwegian Social Science Data Services (NSD)|language=Norwegian|accessdate=28 February 2013}}</ref>
He died in 1990.<ref name=aft/>
