'''Timoléon C. Brutus''' (1886&ndash;1971) was a [[Haiti]]an politician and historian. He served as [[foreign minister]] of Haiti from 1946 to 1949. As a historian, Brutus wrote books about the leaders of the [[Haitian Revolution]], [[Toussaint L'Ouverture]] and [[Jean-Jacques Dessalines]]. His most well-known works are ''Ranςon du Génie ou la Leςon de Toussaint Louverture'' (1945) and ''L'homme d'Airain'' (1946). His son, [[Edner Brutus]], also became a prominent politician and historian.

